    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Louisville, Kentucky</placeName>, <date>February 17,
                    1851</date></p>
            <p>Most honored <addressee>Mr. Leeser</addressee>:</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I hope that you have already received my letter and the<lb/>
                newspapers dispatched to you several days later. I write this letter<lb/> only to
                prove to you that, in spite of all my trouble and my small<lb/> persuasive powers, I
                could do very little up to now, For the “Advocate<add>?</add><lb/> I have obtained,
                outside of myself, only two others, among them <persName>Mr.<lb/> Bernas</persName>.
                Still, I have no doubt that after this newspaper appears<lb/> and answers the need
                of the time, I shall find more subscribers<lb/> for it. for the “Occident”, I have
                four new ones, perhaps even<lb/> five. On the other hand, it seems to me that others
                because of<lb/> economy, <del>be</del> intend to discontinue it. In general, the
                people here<lb/> are too uncultured, to value such an undertaking, or even<lb/>
                merely to understand it. Those who do understand it are<lb/> too indifferent and too
                cold towards religion and Judaism<lb/> to have any interest toward such
                publications. Such, here<lb/>
                <persName>Mr. Leeser</persName>, is usually the case. In the course of the last
                    d<add>?</add><lb/> I have sold fourteen to fifteen prayer books for you.
                    <add>?</add><lb/> these, six for the congregation and several for Christians.
                I<lb/> ask you to send them as soon as possible. You may send two doz<lb/> in
                ordinary binding and two of the finest. Send them to me<lb/> address at as low a
                price as possible, less sending them. Please<lb/> let me know. In the meantime, I
                shall collect for the “Oc<lb/>cident” for I have neglected to do so while looking
                for sub-<lb/>scribers. After delivering the prayer books, I shall send you as<lb/>
                much money as possible.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Looking forward to your immediate reply, I sign</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Most respectfully,</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Your most obedient servant and friend</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">
                <persName role="author">B. H. Gotthelf</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
